%section#comments
  %h1 Comments
  %h3 Posting a comment
  .row
    .col-sm-7
      %p You can add your voice to a discussion using the comment box at the bottom of a discussion page.
      %h3 Markdown
      %p Loomio uses <strong>Markdown</strong> to let you format text and embed images. Check the box next to the word <strong>“Markdown”</strong> under the comment box to turn it on. Click <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.loomio.org%2Fd%2FWh7vHaTk%2Fmarkdown-text-formatting-made-easy&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNF1G0JmE_4DyVNLoCYNALqJYjfILghere">here</a> for information on how to use Markdown.
    .col-sm-5
      =image_tag "comment-box.png", class: "screenshot"
  %h3 Attaching files
  .row
    .col-sm-10
      %p You can attach a file to a comment by clicking the paperclip icon underneath the comment box and selecting the file from your device.
    .col-sm-1
      =image_tag "attachment.png", class: "screenshot"
  %h3 @mentioning group members
  .row
    .col-sm-6
      %p If you want to get the attention of a specific person in your group, type <strong>‘@’</strong> followed by their name. Loomio will autocomplete their username. They will be notified that you’ve mentioned them in a comment.
    .col-sm-6
      =image_tag "mentioning.png", class: "screenshot"
  %h3 Editing a comment
  .row
    .col-sm-10
      %p To allow for fixing typos, you can edit a comment after it is posted. Group coordinators can also configure groups to allow users to edit their comments at any time. The pencil icon for editing a comment will be visible in the right-hand corner of the comment if you have permission to edit it.
    .col-sm-2
      =image_tag "edit-comment.png", class: "screenshot"
  %h3 Liking a comment
  .row
    .col-sm-7
      %p Clicking <strong>“Like”</strong> below a comment is a simple way to let other members of your group that you enjoy or understand what they’ve said without leaving a comment.
    .col-sm-5
      =image_tag "comment-like.png", class: "screenshot"
  .row
    .col-sm-7
      %p When you <strong>“Like”</strong> a comment, the fact that you <strong>“Liked”</strong> it will be visible below the comment. You can undo that action by clicking <strong>“Unlike”</strong> on a comment you’ve previously liked.
    .col-sm-5
      =image_tag "liked-comment.png", class: "screenshot"
  %h3 Deleting a comment
  .row
    .col-sm-10
      %p Members can delete their own comments at any time by clicking the <strong>"X"</strong> in the right-hand corner of the comment. Group coordinators can delete any comments posted in discussions taking place in their group.
    .col-sm-2
      =image_tag "delete-comment.png", class: "screenshot"
